Good morning.

00:00:23.898 --> 00:00:25.650 position:50% align:center
Good morning, Komichi.

00:00:37.746 --> 00:00:39.497 position:50% align:center
Morning, Erika.

00:00:39.581 --> 00:00:41.124 position:50% align:center
[BOTH giggle]

00:00:41.207 --> 00:00:42.334 position:50% align:center
Oh, guess what?

00:00:42.417 --> 00:00:44.085 position:50% align:center
I shared all the pics
we took at the lake

00:00:44.169 --> 00:00:45.879 position:50% align:center
the other day with my dad.

00:00:45.962 --> 00:00:47.630 position:50% align:center
Yeah? And what did
he say about 'em?

00:00:47.714 --> 00:00:49.382 position:50% align:center
He texted back saying he wishes

00:00:49.466 --> 00:00:51.718 position:50% align:center
he could've joined
us on Saturday!

00:00:51.801 --> 00:00:54.262 position:50% align:center
He was super impressed
by your gear, too.

00:00:54.346 --> 00:00:55.805 position:50% align:center
Don't remind me.

00:00:55.889 --> 00:00:58.266 position:50% align:center
I looked like some
kind of fishing fanatic.

00:00:58.350 --> 00:01:02.270 position:50% align:center
And get this, he said
you have very nice hands.

00:01:02.354 --> 00:01:04.064 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:01:04.147 --> 00:01:06.232 position:50% align:center
[ERIKA]
Are they really that nice?

00:01:06.316 --> 00:01:08.735 position:50% align:center
Your hands and nails
are pretty much perfect!

00:01:08.818 --> 00:01:11.112 position:50% align:center
So, I said,

00:01:11.196 --> 00:01:13.448 position:50% align:center
"Well, duh, Erika
plays the violin!"

00:01:13.531 --> 00:01:17.869 position:50% align:center
I wish I was cool enough
to play! I'm so jelly!

00:01:17.952 --> 00:01:19.537 position:50% align:center
[ERIKA]
Says the dancer.

00:01:19.621 --> 00:01:20.747 position:50% align:center
I think that's much cooler

00:01:20.830 --> 00:01:23.500 position:50% align:center
than being able to play
a violin, Komichi.

00:01:23.583 --> 00:01:24.959 position:50% align:center
No way!

00:01:25.043 --> 00:01:26.086 position:50% align:center
[ERIKA]
Yes way.

00:01:26.169 --> 00:01:29.422 position:50% align:center
Ah... Aw, come on.

00:01:29.506 --> 00:01:35.929 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI humming]

00:01:36.012 --> 00:01:36.805 position:50% align:center
Morning.

00:01:36.888 --> 00:01:38.348 position:50% align:center
Morning.

00:01:38.431 --> 00:01:39.683 position:50% align:center
Hello!

00:03:11.232 --> 00:03:13.818 position:50% align:center
[KEI]
Okay, club time. Let's go.

00:03:13.902 --> 00:03:20.033 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS chattering]

00:03:20.116 --> 00:03:21.117 position:50% align:center
[AYUMI]
Yeah, when we're done.

00:03:21.201 --> 00:03:22.827 position:50% align:center
I'll see you back
at the dorm, okay?

00:03:22.911 --> 00:03:25.872 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Mm.

00:03:25.955 --> 00:03:29.125 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS chattering]

00:03:35.298 --> 00:03:38.426 position:50% align:center
[electric guitar playing]

00:03:38.510 --> 00:03:40.220 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Huh?

00:03:43.306 --> 00:03:44.140 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Wow.

00:03:44.224 --> 00:03:46.643 position:50% align:center
Electric guitars sound so sick!

00:03:47.644 --> 00:03:49.771 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 7C]
Oh, come on!

00:03:49.854 --> 00:03:51.856 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 7D]
No, seriously, that was awesome!

00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:53.149 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 7E]
Just do it like that!

00:03:53.233 --> 00:03:54.567 position:50% align:center
It was great!

00:03:54.651 --> 00:03:56.361 position:50% align:center
You got this!

00:03:56.444 --> 00:03:59.280 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU] Seems like everyone
but me has joined a club.

00:04:08.707 --> 00:04:10.750 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Huh? Ed's ranked tenth?

00:04:10.834 --> 00:04:12.502 position:50% align:center
Totally rigged.

00:04:12.585 --> 00:04:15.171 position:50% align:center
Miki's bio will be featured
on the next issue.

00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:18.633 position:50% align:center
Ugh, boo! Who friggin' cares?

00:04:18.717 --> 00:04:21.720 position:50% align:center
Oh, man, this Rara
model guitar is crazy.

00:04:21.803 --> 00:04:23.388 position:50% align:center
--I bet that sound's killer.
--[KOMICHI] Um, excuse me?

00:04:23.471 --> 00:04:26.766 position:50% align:center
Hebimori? Yoohoo!

00:04:26.850 --> 00:04:28.268 position:50% align:center
Am I interrupting?

00:04:28.351 --> 00:04:29.894 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:04:31.396 --> 00:04:32.814 position:50% align:center
Those are pretty hardcore.

00:04:32.897 --> 00:04:36.943 position:50% align:center
Uh, thanks. I didn't
see you there.

00:04:37.027 --> 00:04:39.738 position:50% align:center
Not to pry, whatcha
readin' there?

00:04:43.616 --> 00:04:44.701 position:50% align:center
I knew it!

00:04:44.784 --> 00:04:47.078 position:50% align:center
Aren't music geniuses
into reading that?

00:04:47.162 --> 00:04:48.455 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Huh?

00:04:48.538 --> 00:04:50.957 position:50% align:center
Miki was featured on one issue,
so I snatched it up!

00:04:51.041 --> 00:04:52.459 position:50% align:center
But, then, when I opened it,

00:04:52.542 --> 00:04:56.004 position:50% align:center
I was kinda bummed to see it
only had sheet music inside.

00:04:56.087 --> 00:04:58.882 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU] Huh, she's right.
I didn't even notice.

00:04:58.965 --> 00:05:00.425 position:50% align:center
I can't even read that stuff,

00:05:00.508 --> 00:05:03.094 position:50% align:center
let alone play an
instrument of any kind.

00:05:03.178 --> 00:05:06.056 position:50% align:center
Ooh! But which instrument
do you play, Hebimori?

00:05:06.139 --> 00:05:08.183 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Uh, which?

00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:14.481 position:50% align:center
I play the guitar. Kinda.

00:05:14.564 --> 00:05:19.402 position:50% align:center
Will you please
play it for me, please?

00:05:19.486 --> 00:05:21.905 position:50% align:center
Let me hear you play!

00:05:25.325 --> 00:05:27.327 position:50% align:center
Sure.

00:05:27.410 --> 00:05:29.371 position:50% align:center
[DRAMA CLUB PRESIDENT 4A]
Uh. I'm looking for a lost

00:05:29.454 --> 00:05:30.997 position:50% align:center
Akebi Komichi of
Class-1 to 3.

00:05:31.081 --> 00:05:33.917 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI] Oh, no, prez!
Yikes, I gotta get going!

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.211 position:50% align:center
Poke me when you're
ready to play!

00:05:36.294 --> 00:05:38.296 position:50% align:center
[DRAMA CLUB PRESIDENT 4A]
Again: Akebi Komichi,

00:05:38.380 --> 00:05:41.049 position:50% align:center
--Akebi Komichi, please repor--
--Ugh.

00:05:42.384 --> 00:05:45.261 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Way to go, me.

00:05:45.345 --> 00:05:48.932 position:50% align:center
How can I play when I can't
even read sheet music.

00:05:59.651 --> 00:06:02.779 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU] I brought my dad's old
guitar with me when I moved,

00:06:02.862 --> 00:06:05.281 position:50% align:center
and I haven't
picked it up since.

00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:07.909 position:50% align:center
It's just been sitting
over there in the corner,

00:06:07.992 --> 00:06:10.203 position:50% align:center
collecting dust.

00:06:10.286 --> 00:06:12.956 position:50% align:center
Lame. It's not even electric.

00:06:19.254 --> 00:06:20.839 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:23.425 --> 00:06:25.468 position:50% align:center
Ooh...

00:06:28.555 --> 00:06:31.474 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Hm? Chords?

00:06:31.558 --> 00:06:34.811 position:50% align:center
Just skip to the
"do, re, mi, fa, so" stuff.

00:06:38.106 --> 00:06:40.525 position:50% align:center
Here we go. Okay.

00:06:40.608 --> 00:06:43.111 position:50% align:center
First is... do.

00:06:45.196 --> 00:06:48.742 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Mm. Okay, next.

00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:57.125 position:50% align:center
[guitar playing]

00:06:57.208 --> 00:06:58.793 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
I did it!

00:06:58.877 --> 00:07:01.629 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:07:07.510 --> 00:07:09.095 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Yo, what's up?

00:07:09.179 --> 00:07:10.472 position:50% align:center
Hey.

00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:19.105 position:50% align:center
I always thought that
was just for decoration.

00:07:20.940 --> 00:07:24.402 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU] I figured I should
start learning to play.

00:07:24.486 --> 00:07:26.237 position:50% align:center
Is that cool?

00:07:26.321 --> 00:07:28.573 position:50% align:center
I'll only play when I'm alone.

00:07:28.656 --> 00:07:29.949 position:50% align:center
[MAI]
Doesn't bother me.

00:07:30.033 --> 00:07:33.411 position:50% align:center
Keep it up.

00:07:33.495 --> 00:07:34.829 position:50% align:center
I will.

00:07:51.262 --> 00:07:53.223 position:50% align:center
[FITNESS INSTRUCTOR 7A]
Now, stretch your arms out wide,

00:07:53.306 --> 00:07:56.101 position:50% align:center
and bring your hands together
to touch the clouds.

00:07:56.184 --> 00:07:58.269 position:50% align:center
[KAO]
Touch the clouds!

00:07:58.353 --> 00:08:00.939 position:50% align:center
[phone chimes]

00:08:01.022 --> 00:08:03.400 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
She said she plays the guitar!

00:08:08.071 --> 00:08:10.323 position:50% align:center
[phone chimes]

00:08:10.407 --> 00:08:13.076 position:50% align:center
[SATO] It's never too late
to pick up an instrument.

00:08:14.661 --> 00:08:18.248 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah? Could be fun!

00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:20.291 position:50% align:center
Focus! No phones!

00:08:20.375 --> 00:08:21.626 position:50% align:center
[FITNESS INSTRUCTOR 7A]
Next, raise yourself--

00:08:24.879 --> 00:08:26.172 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL COACH 7A]
Next.

00:08:34.931 --> 00:08:36.182 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL COACH 7A]
Next.

00:08:37.183 --> 00:08:42.022 position:50% align:center
[DRAMA CLUB PRESIDENT 4A]
Ah, eh, ih, ooh, eh, oh, ah, oh!

00:08:42.105 --> 00:08:46.484 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Ah, eh, ih, ooh, eh, oh, ah, oh!

00:08:46.568 --> 00:08:47.944 position:50% align:center
[DRAMA CLUB PRESIDENT 4A]
From the diaphragm!

00:08:48.028 --> 00:08:50.321 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Ah, eh, ih, ooh.

00:08:50.405 --> 00:08:52.323 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL CLUB MEMBER 7A]
Nice work.

00:08:52.407 --> 00:08:53.616 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL CLUB MEMBER 7B]
Yeah, keep it up.

00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:55.076 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL CLUB MEMBER 7C]
Thanks, you, too.

00:08:56.786 --> 00:08:58.038 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL CLUB MEMBER 7D]
Good job.

00:08:58.121 --> 00:09:02.000 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Ooh! Eh! Oh! Ah! Oh!

00:09:02.083 --> 00:09:04.002 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:09:04.085 --> 00:09:07.047 position:50% align:center
Right. Let's break for today.

00:09:07.130 --> 00:09:11.217 position:50% align:center
Yay. Thank you very much.

00:09:11.301 --> 00:09:12.552 position:50% align:center
[DRAMA CLUB PRESIDENT 4A]
Get yourself cleaned up

00:09:12.635 --> 00:09:13.762 position:50% align:center
and head home.

00:09:16.473 --> 00:09:17.265 position:50% align:center
[MAI]
That looked brutal.

00:09:17.349 --> 00:09:19.851 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Oh, Togano.

00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:24.898 position:50% align:center
[MAI] Didn't know drama club
could be so intense.

00:09:24.981 --> 00:09:28.068 position:50% align:center
Do you always practice out here?

00:09:28.151 --> 00:09:30.570 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI] Mm-mm. Mainly
in the lesson room.

00:09:30.653 --> 00:09:33.573 position:50% align:center
But, Prez said I should
try other spots.

00:09:33.656 --> 00:09:35.116 position:50% align:center
What was it?

00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:39.287 position:50% align:center
Well, "All the world's a stage;
your voice, the instrument."

00:09:39.371 --> 00:09:42.082 position:50% align:center
[laughs] Sounds pretty good.

00:09:42.165 --> 00:09:45.085 position:50% align:center
Not bad, but I'm still
learning the foundations.

00:09:45.168 --> 00:09:49.089 position:50% align:center
I've gotta be at my peak
before the school play!

00:09:49.172 --> 00:09:53.551 position:50% align:center
To build up my trunk,
at home, I do this.

00:09:53.635 --> 00:09:54.761 position:50% align:center
I get it.

00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:57.472 position:50% align:center
It's hard keeping up
with all the pressure.

00:09:57.555 --> 00:09:59.140 position:50% align:center
And it's fun, too!

00:09:59.224 --> 00:10:01.017 position:50% align:center
Doesn't learning something
you couldn't do before

00:10:01.101 --> 00:10:04.771 position:50% align:center
make all that hard work
totally worth it?

00:10:04.854 --> 00:10:05.897 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:10:07.732 --> 00:10:08.733 position:50% align:center
Oh, that's right!

00:10:08.817 --> 00:10:10.318 position:50% align:center
Don't you and
Hebimori live together

00:10:10.402 --> 00:10:12.404 position:50% align:center
over in the Mangetsu dorm?

00:10:12.487 --> 00:10:14.280 position:50% align:center
[MAI]
We're roommates.

00:10:14.364 --> 00:10:16.032 position:50% align:center
Wow! So, you get to hear her

00:10:16.116 --> 00:10:19.703 position:50% align:center
rock out on the guitar,
like, every day?

00:10:19.786 --> 00:10:21.204 position:50% align:center
[MAI]
Huh?

00:10:25.959 --> 00:10:31.256 position:50% align:center
G chord, and uh,
first string, third fret.

00:10:31.339 --> 00:10:33.842 position:50% align:center
Fifth string, second fret.

00:10:33.925 --> 00:10:36.970 position:50% align:center
Sixth string, third fret.

00:10:37.053 --> 00:10:42.392 position:50% align:center
They make it sound easy.
Am I even doing this right?

00:10:42.475 --> 00:10:46.563 position:50% align:center
Whatever. Next is C.

00:10:47.564 --> 00:10:50.150 position:50% align:center
Second string, first fret.

00:10:50.233 --> 00:10:52.902 position:50% align:center
Fourth string, second fret.

00:10:52.986 --> 00:10:55.280 position:50% align:center
Fifth string, third fret.

00:10:55.363 --> 00:10:59.200 position:50% align:center
And Sixth string... mute?

00:10:59.284 --> 00:11:00.994 position:50% align:center
Wait, what?

00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:02.328 position:50% align:center
How many chords
do I have to learn

00:11:02.412 --> 00:11:04.289 position:50% align:center
for one friggin' song?

00:11:12.422 --> 00:11:14.591 position:50% align:center
Yeah, no.

00:11:14.674 --> 00:11:17.135 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Time to cut some corners.

00:11:17.218 --> 00:11:19.554 position:50% align:center
Focus on the
important ones only.

00:11:30.732 --> 00:11:32.942 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Hey, what's up?

00:11:33.026 --> 00:11:34.361 position:50% align:center
Nothing much.

00:11:34.444 --> 00:11:38.865 position:50% align:center
Cool. I broke out your favorite
if you wanna go a round?

00:11:40.492 --> 00:11:44.371 position:50% align:center
Hey, so, I saw
Akebi after practice.

00:11:44.454 --> 00:11:47.165 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh.

00:11:47.248 --> 00:11:50.919 position:50% align:center
She seems stoked to
hear you play the guitar.

00:11:51.002 --> 00:11:54.047 position:50% align:center
So why aren't you practicing?

00:11:54.130 --> 00:11:55.590 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
You know, apparently,

00:11:55.674 --> 00:11:59.386 position:50% align:center
there are different
ways to play a guitar.

00:11:59.469 --> 00:12:03.181 position:50% align:center
Those chords, C, E, and F,
were short-circuiting my brain.

00:12:03.264 --> 00:12:06.309 position:50% align:center
And hitting the books was
never really my style anyway.

00:12:06.393 --> 00:12:08.812 position:50% align:center
There's no way
I can play the guitar.

00:12:08.895 --> 00:12:12.732 position:50% align:center
Huh. And when did you plan
to let Akebi know that?

00:12:17.529 --> 00:12:20.532 position:50% align:center
All I did was turn a screw.

00:12:20.615 --> 00:12:22.951 position:50% align:center
[MAI]
The strings did look rusty.

00:12:23.034 --> 00:12:25.412 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
See? Neglecting my instrument

00:12:25.495 --> 00:12:27.747 position:50% align:center
proves that I'm not
cut out for this.

00:12:27.831 --> 00:12:29.416 position:50% align:center
So that's it?

00:12:29.499 --> 00:12:32.544 position:50% align:center
Guitar's busted.
Even if I did wanna play,

00:12:32.627 --> 00:12:33.628 position:50% align:center
what's the point?

00:12:33.712 --> 00:12:36.131 position:50% align:center
Guess I'll just
throw in the towel.

00:12:36.214 --> 00:12:40.135 position:50% align:center
Even pros had to get
their start somewhere.

00:12:40.218 --> 00:12:41.428 position:50% align:center
Learning chords.

00:12:41.511 --> 00:12:43.555 position:50% align:center
Or shooting hoops every day.

00:12:51.688 --> 00:12:53.273 position:50% align:center
I win again.

00:12:54.524 --> 00:12:56.985 position:50% align:center
Woah. So pro.

00:13:01.823 --> 00:13:02.824 position:50% align:center
[TENNIS CLUB MEMBER 7B]
Nice! Over here!

00:13:02.907 --> 00:13:04.075 position:50% align:center
[TENNIS CLUB MEMBER 7C]
Good one!

00:13:04.159 --> 00:13:05.326 position:50% align:center
[TENNIS CLUB MEMBER 7B]
Okay, move your feet!

00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:07.620 position:50% align:center
[TENNIS CLUB MEMBER 7C]
One more! Oh, nice hit!

00:13:13.752 --> 00:13:17.088 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU] Tatsumori.
I didn't know she ran track.

00:13:17.172 --> 00:13:19.341 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Ah, eh, ih, ooh...

00:13:19.424 --> 00:13:20.592 position:50% align:center
[DRAMA CLUB PRESIDENT 4A]
Nice work!

00:13:20.675 --> 00:13:24.387 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI] Ah, oh, ah, eh,
ih, ooh, eh, oh...

00:13:24.471 --> 00:13:25.805 position:50% align:center
[DRAMA CLUB PRESIDENT 4A]
Remember, from the belly!

00:13:25.889 --> 00:13:27.265 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Ah, eh, ih, ooh...

00:13:27.349 --> 00:13:28.933 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Akebi.

00:13:31.478 --> 00:13:33.563 position:50% align:center
[DRAMA CLUB PRESIDENT 4A]
Much better than yesterday.

00:13:33.646 --> 00:13:36.941 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU] I mean, wow.
She's drenched in sweat.

00:13:37.025 --> 00:13:38.777 position:50% align:center
That look on her face.

00:13:59.464 --> 00:14:00.757 position:50% align:center
[BASKETBALL COACH 7A]
Nice, Togano.

00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:03.009 position:50% align:center
Next practice, cover the
floor as a forward, got it?

00:14:03.093 --> 00:14:04.761 position:50% align:center
Yeah!

00:14:04.844 --> 00:14:06.721 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Togano, too.

00:14:15.689 --> 00:14:17.232 position:50% align:center
I did it!

00:14:27.659 --> 00:14:29.160 position:50% align:center
[MAI]
When I first started playing,

00:14:29.244 --> 00:14:32.330 position:50% align:center
I couldn't even graze
the net with the ball.

00:14:32.414 --> 00:14:33.456 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:34.958 position:50% align:center
[MAI]
Know why?

00:14:35.041 --> 00:14:36.835 position:50% align:center
Cuz' I was trying to make
long shots right off the bat.

00:14:36.918 --> 00:14:39.587 position:50% align:center
That sounds... not smart at all.

00:14:39.671 --> 00:14:42.966 position:50% align:center
Yeah, and I still miss
a lot of my shots.

00:14:43.049 --> 00:14:45.343 position:50% align:center
But when I started
shooting closer to the net,

00:14:45.427 --> 00:14:48.805 position:50% align:center
my aim gradually got better.

00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:52.350 position:50% align:center
Maybe you've aimed too high.

00:14:53.435 --> 00:14:56.604 position:50% align:center
And the song you
picked is too hard.

00:15:00.150 --> 00:15:02.068 position:50% align:center
I know this song.

00:16:03.254 --> 00:16:10.595 position:50% align:center
[guitar playing]

00:16:38.081 --> 00:16:39.874 position:50% align:center
Ready to go?

00:16:39.958 --> 00:16:41.209 position:50% align:center
Uh--

00:16:48.216 --> 00:16:49.009 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Morning!

00:16:49.092 --> 00:16:51.469 position:50% align:center
Morning.

00:16:51.553 --> 00:16:54.222 position:50% align:center
Uh, Akebi?

00:16:54.305 --> 00:16:59.436 position:50% align:center
Um. Do you, uh, have time
to meet up after class?

00:17:02.188 --> 00:17:04.566 position:50% align:center
Anyone here?

00:17:04.649 --> 00:17:07.235 position:50% align:center
I'm so excited.
I'm getting nervous.

00:17:07.318 --> 00:17:09.487 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU] Hey, I'm the one
that's playing here.

00:17:09.571 --> 00:17:10.989 position:50% align:center
You got this!

00:17:12.574 --> 00:17:15.869 position:50% align:center
Yeah, hope so.

00:17:18.997 --> 00:17:20.582 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU, KOMICHI gasp]

00:17:55.575 --> 00:18:00.580 position:50% align:center
♪

00:18:23.812 --> 00:18:25.522 position:50% align:center
[door opens]

00:18:25.605 --> 00:18:28.316 position:50% align:center
Ha! Hiding in the
music room, Kizaki?

00:18:28.400 --> 00:18:30.402 position:50% align:center
Uh-- I'm not hiding!

00:18:30.485 --> 00:18:31.903 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
That's Erika on piano?

00:18:31.986 --> 00:18:33.571 position:50% align:center
[ERIKA]
...on cleaning duty this week.

00:18:33.655 --> 00:18:36.116 position:50% align:center
[TOUKO]
Oh, yeah, right!

00:18:36.199 --> 00:18:39.119 position:50% align:center
Need something? Make it
quick, I've got club.

00:18:39.202 --> 00:18:42.872 position:50% align:center
[TOUKO]
Don't make that face! Rude!

00:18:42.956 --> 00:18:44.666 position:50% align:center
Poor Ai can't even
walk into your room

00:18:44.749 --> 00:18:47.794 position:50% align:center
without a major meltdown
about her bothering you.

00:18:47.877 --> 00:18:51.297 position:50% align:center
So, I volunteered as tribute
to humbly leave word.

00:18:51.381 --> 00:18:52.298 position:50% align:center
[ERIKA]
Huh?

00:18:52.382 --> 00:18:53.633 position:50% align:center
Fear not.

00:18:53.717 --> 00:18:55.301 position:50% align:center
When you're mad, I told her
you get super scary

00:18:55.385 --> 00:18:57.178 position:50% align:center
around everyone, not just her!

00:18:57.262 --> 00:18:59.514 position:50% align:center
Shut up, I'm not scary at all!

00:18:59.597 --> 00:19:01.516 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh. See what I mean?

00:19:01.599 --> 00:19:03.685 position:50% align:center
And I'm not like
that to everyone.

00:19:03.768 --> 00:19:05.770 position:50% align:center
[TOUKO]
Wait, then who...?

00:19:07.731 --> 00:19:10.734 position:50% align:center
That's the first time
I've seen Erika like that.

00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:16.573 position:50% align:center
But, her playing was beautiful.

00:19:16.656 --> 00:19:18.074 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Sorry.

00:19:20.285 --> 00:19:22.328 position:50% align:center
I'm honestly not up to this.

00:19:22.412 --> 00:19:24.622 position:50% align:center
Besides, I can't follow that.

00:19:24.706 --> 00:19:26.082 position:50% align:center
She's a real musician, not me.

00:19:26.166 --> 00:19:27.667 position:50% align:center
Wait, come back!

00:19:27.751 --> 00:19:30.837 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
It was a lie, Akebi. I'm sorry.

00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:34.382 position:50% align:center
The truth is,
I can't play the guitar.

00:19:34.466 --> 00:19:35.842 position:50% align:center
I'm leaving.

00:19:38.178 --> 00:19:42.140 position:50% align:center
Stay! Please, let me hear it.

00:20:01.618 --> 00:20:06.623 position:50% align:center
♪

00:21:14.357 --> 00:21:15.775 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:21:21.072 --> 00:21:22.574 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:21:27.579 --> 00:21:30.331 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
No, that sounded kind of off.

00:21:33.918 --> 00:21:34.753 position:50% align:center
Nice!

00:21:34.836 --> 00:21:35.920 position:50% align:center
What?

00:21:36.004 --> 00:21:40.342 position:50% align:center
Uh-- Togano. Finally
nailed the F-chord.

00:21:40.425 --> 00:21:43.970 position:50% align:center
Con... grats?

00:21:44.054 --> 00:21:48.183 position:50% align:center
Uh! It's crazy hard!
But I'm gonna give Akebi

00:21:48.266 --> 00:21:53.521 position:50% align:center
a much better performance
the next time I play for her.

00:21:53.605 --> 00:21:55.273 position:50% align:center
Can you do it again?

00:21:55.357 --> 00:21:56.566 position:50% align:center
[OSHIZU]
Huh?

00:21:56.649 --> 00:21:58.568 position:50% align:center
Play the F chord?

00:21:58.651 --> 00:22:02.530 position:50% align:center
Sure. Since you asked so nicely.

00:22:02.614 --> 00:22:04.741 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI] I got to hear
both Kizaki and Hebimori

00:22:04.824 --> 00:22:07.118 position:50% align:center
play their instruments today!

00:22:07.202 --> 00:22:11.289 position:50% align:center
It actually made me wanna work
even harder in drama club!

00:22:11.373 --> 00:22:13.792 position:50% align:center
No phone zone!
Time to stretch, Komi!

00:22:13.875 --> 00:22:15.210 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Okay!

00:22:15.293 --> 00:22:17.003 position:50% align:center
[FITNESS INSTRUCTOR 7A]
Now, stretch your arms out wide,

00:22:17.087 --> 00:22:20.131 position:50% align:center
and bring your hands together
to touch the clouds.

00:22:20.215 --> 00:22:22.175 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Touch the clouds!